  "title": "Structure of a fully assembled tumor-specific T cell receptor ligated by pMHC.",
  "journal": "Cell",
  "year": 2022,
  "authors": "Su\u0161ac L, Vuong MT, Thomas C, von B\u00fclow S, O'Brien-Ball C, Santos AM, Fernandes RA, Hummer G, Tamp\u00e9 R, Davis SJ."
 },
 "executive_summary": "This study determined the cryo-EM structure of a tumor-reactive human \u03b1\u03b2TCR (origin and specificity not specified beyond \"melanoma-specific\") bound to a class I pMHC, capturing the complete 11-subunit TCR/CD3 signaling complex at 3.08 \u00c5 resolution. The structure reveals how multivalent interactions across three layers stabilize the complex, including a role for membrane-embedded sterol lipids in TCR assembly and clustered cysteines stabilizing the CD3 heterodimers. The work establishes the spatial geometry required for T cells to scan antigen-presenting cell membranes efficiently and demonstrates that TCR triggering can occur without large conformational rearrangements in the ligand-bound state. These insights into how tumor-specific TCRs recognize and bind pMHC are relevant to understanding T cell activation against cancer and may inform rational engineering of TCRs for immunotherapy applications.",
